WITH all_items AS (
  SELECT 
    oi.item_id,
    oi.product_id,
    COALESCE(c.name, 'No Category') AS category_name
  FROM order_items oi
  JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id

)

-- 02_unique_returns.sql
```sql
WITH unique_returns AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT ON (item_id)
    item_id,
    return_date
  FROM returns
  ORDER BY item_id, 
    CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END,
    return_date
)
SELECT * FROM unique_returns;
```

-- 03_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
WITH all_items AS (
  SELECT 
    oi.item_id,
    COALESCE(c.name, 'No Category') AS category_name
  FROM order_items oi
  JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id
  LEFT JOIN categories c ON p.category_id = c.category_id
),
unique_returns AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT ON (item_id)
    item_id
  FROM returns
  ORDER BY item_id, 
    CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END,
    return_date
)
SELECT 
  ai.category_name,
  COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
  COUNT(ur.item_id) AS total_items_returned,
  ROUND(COUNT(ur.item_id)::numeric / COUNT(*), 4) AS return_rate
FROM all_items ai
LEFT JOIN unique_returns ur ON ai.item_id = ur.item_id
GROUP BY ai.category_name
ORDER BY ai.category_name;
